# Next.js App Router Patterns

## Page Components
- Use `page.tsx` for route pages
- Export as default: `export default function PageName()`
- Use proper metadata exports for SEO

## Layout Components
- Use `layout.tsx` for shared layouts
- Export metadata and layout components
- Handle client-side features with "use client"

## Authentication Pages
- Place in `src/app/auth/` directory
- Use shadcn/ui Card components for forms
- Include proper form validation
- Use environment variables for configuration

## API Routes
- Use `route.ts` files for API endpoints
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Include proper error handling
- Use TypeScript for request/response types

## File Naming
- Use kebab-case for directories: `auth/sign-in/`
- Use `page.tsx` for pages
- Use `layout.tsx` for layouts
- Use `route.ts` for API routes

## Metadata
```typescript
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: "Page Title",
  description: "Page description",
};
```

## Client Components
- Add "use client" directive when needed
- Use for interactive features, state, effects
- Keep server components as default